WorldStage Newsonline– Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo State has been unanimously nominated to chair the National Economic Council (NEC)  Ad-Hoc Committee On Crude Oil Theft Prevention And Control The decision at the 92nd NEC Meeting on Thursday is for him to replace the former Governor of Delta State, Dr. Emmanuel Oduaghan. Under the new leadership, the Committee proceeded to give an updated report to the Council at a later date. Members of the Committee include Governors of Akwa Ibom, Delta, Bayelsa, Cross River and Ondo.  The Budget and Planning, Finance and Petroleum Resources Ministers, and the representatives from all the Security Organisations, EFCC and the International Oil Companies will also be on the Committee.